elements.name: Verify Information Icon on KiwiSaver Calculator

steps.name: The user open a browser, enters to Westpac New Zealand Limited website
navigates to KiwiSaver > KiwiSaver calculators > Click here to get started button
The user clicks on information icon besides the "Employment Status" field

message "If you are earning a salary or wage, select ‘Employed’. Your employer contributions will be automatically calculated at a rate of 3% of your before-tax salary or wages. You can also select ‘Self-employed’ or ‘Not employed’ and then enter below (in the Voluntary contributions field), the amount and frequency of any contributions that you wish to make." is displayed below the "Employment Status" field

arguments.val: "If you are earning a salary or wage, select ‘Employed’. Your employer contributions will be automatically calculated at a rate of 3% of your before-tax salary or wages. You can also select ‘Self-employed’ or ‘Not employed’ and then enter below (in the Voluntary contributions field), the amount and frequency of any contributions that you wish to make."
